evidence, but it just seems to me that I do a LOT more damage with the lance than I do with the DMF, even when I factor in the additional swings I'd be getting with the DMF. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udelsinionbarlepop.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Delsinion Barlepop</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/23/02 12:40:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=279.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lazykatcreations.com/images/Sdallas_small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weapon Question</span><hr size=1> I ran the numbers for the lance and dmf through a calculator, assuming you have max skill, 170 str and 46% haste.  Shows the DPM being about 51pts or so in favor of the lance... not a large difference.<br><br>I know that when I was in Ssra the other night I was using my lance quite a bit as opposed to my imperial katana simply for the speed of hits since I was hitting for the minimum damage on btm mobs an inordinant amount.  Guess I favor a speedy 2h'er to take advantage of the min damage over a 1hs/shield in most raid situations.<br><br>Here's the damage calculator I used, it seems to be pretty simple and close enough for gaming work <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/luthairsite/weaponCalc.html">www.geocities.com/luthair...nCalc.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>Hate working midshift on fridays, have nothing better to do than troll the boards and offer opinions hehe. <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=83637">Delsinion Barlepop: the pally</a><BR><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=83695">Elewood Ballues: the beastlord</a><BR><BR><a